text:
Closing this bug as it was either fixed as a side effect of other work or it was
due to a scripting error to begin with. The following example shows that the
error described in the original report does not happen anymore.

<?xml version="1.0" standalone="no"?>

<svg width="5cm" height="3cm"  viewBox="0 0 500 300" 
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" version="1.1">

    <a ><rect x="0" y="0" width="100%" height="100%" fill="#0F0"
onmouseover="checkClass(evt)" class="className"/></a>
<script><![CDATA[
    function checkClass(evt) {
    var t = evt.target;
    System.err.println(">>>>>>>>> target's class : " + t.getAttributeNS(null,
"class"));
    }
]]></script>
</svg>
